1
00:00:01,130 --> 00:01:33,130
♪

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:38,030
(laughing)

3
00:01:38,030 --> 00:01:41,110
Men, this is our moment!

4
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:43,110
(cheering)

5
00:01:43,110 --> 00:01:46,120
♪

6
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:50,020
I've gotta get back
and help Raijuta.

7
00:01:50,020 --> 00:01:53,260
(cheering)

8
00:01:53,260 --> 00:01:56,250
(shouting)

9
00:01:56,250 --> 00:02:00,130
(gunshots firing)

10
00:02:00,130 --> 00:02:03,100
(yelling)

11
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:06,080
♪

12
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:08,230
(laughing)

13
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:19,280
♪

14
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,130
I've gotta help Raijuta.

15
00:02:21,130 --> 00:02:23,160
Please don't let
anything happen to him.

16
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:25,280
I'm coming, Sensei.

17
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:31,190
♪

18
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:34,160
(yelling)

19
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:37,200
Fire at will!

20
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:41,110
(gunshots)

21
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:44,080
(yelling)

22
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:56,110
(groaning)

23
00:02:56,110 --> 00:02:59,260
This is awful.

24
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:01,000
Where's Yutaro?

25
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,170
(shouting)

26
00:03:04,170 --> 00:03:10,150
♪

27
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:14,220
(gunshots)

28
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:26,040
♪

29
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,120
Hold your fire!

30
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,190
There's too many rifles,
we don't stand a chance.

31
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:31,170
I think that maybe you're right.

32
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:33,170
There's no way we could
take on all of them.

33
00:03:33,170 --> 00:03:35,200
What are you saying?

34
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:38,020
You knew in order to
build a new kingdom,

35
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:39,260
many of us would have to die.

36
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:43,000
We either fight for what we
believe in, or die cowards.

37
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,140
I'm sorry.

38
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:47,000
It is better to die with honor.

39
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,230
-I won't let them stop us!
-Move in!

40
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:53,200
(shouting)

41
00:03:55,170 --> 00:03:57,020
Fire!

42
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:58,230
Hey, get down!

43
00:03:58,230 --> 00:04:02,180
(grunting)

44
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:06,280
(gunshots firing)

45
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:10,080
(groaning)

46
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:17,240
♪

47
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:22,180
Hold your fire!

48
00:04:22,180 --> 00:04:25,220
(murmuring)

49
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:29,030
♪

50
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:30,270
Stop the killing!

51
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,250
Stop the bloodshed!

52
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:34,180
Stop killing each other!

53
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:37,120
I won't allow this to continue!

54
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,070
Kenshin!

55
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:41,030
Who the hell are you?

56
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:44,160
I will fight against
Raijuta myself.

57
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:46,240
You will wait for the outcome.

58
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,280
Till then there's
to be a ceasefire.

59
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:50,010
Commander!

60
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:52,290
♪

61
00:04:52,290 --> 00:04:54,110
What is it, chief?

62
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:55,230
You should do as Kenshin says,

63
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:58,060
and allow him to fight
Raijuta all alone.

64
00:04:58,060 --> 00:04:59,170
Kenshin?

65
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:03,030
Is that who I think it is?

66
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:04,130
Men!

67
00:05:04,130 --> 00:05:06,070
Hold your fire!

68
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:09,180
Soldiers and samurai,
we ask for a truce.

69
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:14,070
Safety your guns,
and sheathe your swords.

70
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,030
Kenshin!

71
00:05:15,030 --> 00:05:16,140
Come on, you guys,
let's follow him.

72
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:18,090
Mhm.

73
00:05:20,170 --> 00:05:21,180
Sensei Raijuta!

74
00:05:21,180 --> 00:05:24,110
I'm coming to help you,
Sensei, I'm coming!

75
00:05:24,110 --> 00:05:25,170
Sensei?

76
00:05:25,170 --> 00:05:26,240
Huh?

77
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:29,080
(groaning)

78
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,170
Help, I've been shot.

79
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:33,220
Can you get someone to help me?

80
00:05:33,220 --> 00:05:35,250
Uh, wait.

81
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:40,020
I'll help you.

82
00:05:40,020 --> 00:05:42,210
I'm in pain, I need a doctor.

83
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:45,000
Hey, you're that guy.

84
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,250
The one that tried to kidnap me.

85
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:50,070
Wait a minute.

86
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:53,180
I was hired to kidnap you,
I'm sorry I did that,

87
00:05:53,180 --> 00:05:57,040
but Raijuta made us do it,
he ordered us to kidnap you.

88
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,050
-My sensei?
-That's right.

89
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:01,080
He set up the
whole thing himself.

90
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,250
He wanted it to look
like he saved you

91
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:05,070
so you'd be indebted to him.

92
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:06,290
-You're lying!
-It's the truth.

93
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:09,030
All the others
were deceived too.

94
00:06:09,030 --> 00:06:10,060
All the others were killed.

95
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:12,110
I was the only one
to escape alive.

96
00:06:12,110 --> 00:06:15,080
(shouting)

97
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:21,160
(panting)

98
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:31,050
Uh, Sensei.

99
00:06:31,050 --> 00:06:32,090
I'm glad you found me.

100
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:33,290
I've been looking for you.

101
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:37,230
Don't worry, Sensei,
I didn't believe his lies.

102
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:40,160
Don't you know that I
think of you as my father?

103
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:47,170
(gasping)

104
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,090
-Kenshin!
-Yutaro!

105
00:06:52,090 --> 00:06:53,190
Yutaro, come here.

106
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:56,290
So, you're still
alive, Battousai.

107
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:58,150
That's right, Raijuta.

108
00:06:58,150 --> 00:07:00,270
I've come to settle
a score with you.

109
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:02,110
You and I will fight together

110
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:04,110
to put an end to
all of this killing.

111
00:07:04,110 --> 00:07:05,160
What?

112
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:08,180
We are here battling this
army to have our own kingdom.

113
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:11,290
This doesn't concern you.

114
00:07:11,290 --> 00:07:14,060
-It's all right.
-But Raijuta!

115
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:16,060
I will fight him.

116
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:18,040
Kenshin!

117
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,030
They call you Battousai,
but you look like

118
00:07:20,030 --> 00:07:22,200
a scrawny little kid to me.

119
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,290
I will demonstrate
to you, little boy

120
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:27,190
what a real master
swordsman fights like.

121
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,220
Watch and learn.

122
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:31,110
You're about to die.

123
00:07:31,110 --> 00:07:33,100
The Izuna technique.

124
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:37,200
(yelling)

125
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:40,070
(explosions)

126
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:42,080
-Run away!
-We better move!

127
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:48,130
(panting)

128
00:07:48,130 --> 00:07:51,090
-Kenshin!
-Where is he?

129
00:07:51,090 --> 00:07:54,220
(tree branches breaking)

130
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,000
Kenshin!

131
00:07:58,180 --> 00:08:01,150
(whimpering)

132
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:08,280
Not bad, little boy.

133
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:11,030
Next time you
won't be so lucky.

134
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:15,020
Battousai, prepare to die.

135
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,290
(gasping)

136
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:23,170
(water flowing)

137
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:36,140
You're dead!

138
00:08:39,260 --> 00:08:42,130
Please, don't do this!

139
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:43,190
Hm?

140
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:45,060
What is he doing?

141
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,210
Please, Raijuta.

142
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:49,050
Kenshin once saved
me from drowning.

143
00:08:49,050 --> 00:08:50,180
Get away from him.

144
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:53,160
He is a very brave
swordsman, just like you.

145
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:57,240
Sensei, I know that you want
to create your own kingdom,

146
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:02,040
but if you could only talk to
him, I know he'd like you.

147
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:04,200
-Beat it, kid.
-I won't go.

148
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,240
Please, Raijuta, won't
you listen to me?

149
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:08,160
Yutaro, get away from there!

150
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:11,200
Don't you realize by now what
kind of jerk that guy is?

151
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,240
He's not!

152
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,080
I don't want either one
of them to get hurt.

153
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:18,210
(grunting)

154
00:09:18,210 --> 00:09:22,120
(screaming)

155
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:24,290
(gasping)

156
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:27,260
(yelling)

157
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:32,040
No!

158
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,290
Yutaro's hurt!

159
00:09:33,290 --> 00:09:35,220
That bastard!

160
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:37,220
Is he alive?

161
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:42,260
(gasping)

162
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:45,140
Sensei--

163
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:47,160
He didn't mean to.

164
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,280
(grunting)

165
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,290
You!

166
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:53,250
How could you be so heartless?

167
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:55,240
Sensei.

168
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:58,000
This young boy looked up
to you just like a father.

169
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,160
You were his teacher, and
this is how you treat him?

170
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,230
You used him just so you
could build your kingdom.

171
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:05,010
You don't care a
thing about him.

172
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:06,250
Please tell them.

173
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:10,270
Tell them it's not
true what she's saying.

174
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:13,040
So, you think that
she's lying to you?

175
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:16,010
(laughing)

176
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:23,200
Well, she's not, she's
telling the truth!

177
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,040
I don't really give
a damn about you.

178
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:28,080
I just used you so I could use
your house, and your money.

179
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:31,210
As a matter of fact, I have
no reason to keep you alive.

180
00:10:31,210 --> 00:10:34,120
(whimpering)

181
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,150
You're lower than dirt.

182
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:38,170
Yutaro would do
anything for you,

183
00:10:38,170 --> 00:10:40,180
and this is the
way you treat him?

184
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:43,140
You're nothing but a snake.

185
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:47,190
I've met a lot of scumbags in
my time when I was a slasher,

186
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:49,150
but you're the worst one.

187
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:50,190
Kenshin.

188
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:54,140
♪

189
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:58,160
You turned many
samurai into killers.

190
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,120
You toyed with
the heart of a boy

191
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,080
who looked up to
you like a father.

192
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:05,040
♪

193
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,160
Shame on you.

194
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:09,010
You will pay for
everything you've done.

195
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:10,010
Hm?

196
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:15,040
♪

197
00:11:16,210 --> 00:11:27,290
♪

198
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:31,100
(groaning and gasping)

199
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:35,010
Kori, please take Yutaro
to Hannah's place.

200
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:38,060
Have Megumi treat his wound.

201
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:40,200
-All right.
-Sano, please go with her.

202
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,250
Huh?

203
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:43,070
There's still a battle going on.

204
00:11:43,070 --> 00:11:45,090
I want you to go with
them so they're safe.

205
00:11:45,090 --> 00:11:47,270
Please, Sano, go with them and
make sure they're all right.

206
00:11:47,270 --> 00:11:50,200
All right, let's go.

207
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:53,020
-I know the way to Hannah's.
-Okay.

208
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:56,290
-Yoshi, go with them.
-No, I want to see you beat him!

209
00:11:56,290 --> 00:12:01,060
Let me stay here
and see it for Yutaro!

210
00:12:01,060 --> 00:12:04,100
Kenshin, whatever you do,
please make him suffer.

211
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:08,050
Don't worry, he's going down.

212
00:12:08,050 --> 00:12:09,280
Pretty cocky, aren't you?

213
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:13,090
You didn't wound Yutaro
in vain, Raijuta.

214
00:12:13,090 --> 00:12:16,000
I was able to see
your technique,

215
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,090
and you know what,
I'll beat you!

216
00:12:18,090 --> 00:12:20,050
Oh yeah?

217
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:22,250
That bloodless cut you
inflicted on Yutaro

218
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:27,110
using the air to create a
vacuum wave with your sword,

219
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:29,020
we call that the weasel slash.

220
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,220
Hm?

221
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:35,110
And the reason for that is
only weasels like you use it!

222
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:36,080
Oh yeah?

223
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,100
Well, you're nothing
but a puny boy,

224
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,220
and you don't stand
a chance against me.

225
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,280
The great Battousai,
what a joke!

226
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,150
I'll carve you
into little pieces,

227
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:46,220
and feed you to the pigeons.

228
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:49,020
You will be one more dead body

229
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:51,090
to add to my list of conquests.

230
00:12:51,090 --> 00:12:54,160
Ahh, get yourself ready to die!

231
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:58,010
(explosion)

232
00:12:58,010 --> 00:13:13,110
♪

233
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:17,120
(gasping)

234
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:19,260
-Did he get him?
-I'm not really sure.

235
00:13:19,260 --> 00:13:21,270
♪

236
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:24,070
How do you like the
Izuna sword technique?

237
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:28,190
♪

238
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:29,270
Huh?

239
00:13:29,270 --> 00:13:33,070
It doesn't matter how
many times you do it.

240
00:13:33,070 --> 00:13:36,240
Huh?

241
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,220
Your technique comes
through the ground.

242
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:40,260
Your Izuna makes it easy
to calculate its movement,

243
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:43,010
and get out of the way.

244
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:44,170
You're not as dumb as you look!

245
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:46,280
I'll use a flying Izuna.

246
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:48,100
Eat this!

247
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:51,090
(grunting)

248
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:53,220
♪

249
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:55,000
What is that?

250
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,200
I've never seen anything
like that before.

251
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:59,090
That's worse than the other one!

252
00:13:59,090 --> 00:14:02,170
(shouting)

253
00:14:02,170 --> 00:14:25,270
♪

254
00:14:25,270 --> 00:14:28,250
(gasping)

255
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:34,180
(laughing)

256
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:37,270
See that?

257
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:39,120
I can cut you!

258
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:42,230
You're not so
indestructible after all!

259
00:14:42,230 --> 00:14:44,020
Happy now?

260
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:46,000
What's that?

261
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,170
Does this little
scratch make you happy?

262
00:14:48,170 --> 00:14:51,200
-This wound is pathetic.
-You squirt!

263
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:54,080
I'm better than you!

264
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,130
This will be the only wound
you'll inflict on me.

265
00:14:57,130 --> 00:15:00,060
-You're nothing but a maniac!
-Oh yeah?

266
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:03,000
(grunting)

267
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:11,240
♪

268
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:15,020
-Impossible!
-Kenshin!

269
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:16,250
Whoa, Dragon Flash!

270
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:19,240
(yelling)

271
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:25,040
♪

272
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,030
Hiten Mitsurugi style.

273
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:29,010
Dragon hammer flash!

274
00:15:29,010 --> 00:15:31,240
(shouting)

275
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:34,080
I can't!

276
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:43,010
Kenshin, you did it!

277
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:45,250
He was a monster.

278
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:51,070
That's the end of our dream.

279
00:15:51,070 --> 00:15:53,040
With Raijuta dead, I
guess that we'll never

280
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,190
be able to have our kingdom.

281
00:15:57,230 --> 00:16:00,200
(grunting)

282
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:09,000
♪

283
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,240
You can die at any time.

284
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:13,140
It takes true courage to live.

285
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:15,010
Just what does he mean?

286
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:18,070
You are a talented samurai.

287
00:16:18,070 --> 00:16:21,140
Use your abilities
to help people.

288
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:24,210
(crying)

289
00:16:24,210 --> 00:16:32,220
♪

290
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:33,270
So Yoshi, is it true?

291
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:35,120
Did Kenshin win the battle?

292
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,120
Yes, Kenshin beat Raijuta!

293
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,280
The killing's over,
no one else has to die!

294
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:41,140
Unbelievable.

295
00:16:41,140 --> 00:16:44,220
He beat that big
enormous monster Raijuta.

296
00:16:44,220 --> 00:16:47,090
This Kenshin, I
suppose he really is

297
00:16:47,090 --> 00:16:49,030
a living legend after all.

298
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:55,050
♪

299
00:16:55,050 --> 00:16:57,030
He's only wounded
on his right arm.

300
00:16:57,030 --> 00:16:58,150
He should recover.

301
00:16:58,150 --> 00:17:00,210
However, there is one thing.

302
00:17:00,210 --> 00:17:01,240
What's that?

303
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:04,060
The nerves and muscles
are severed on his arm.

304
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:07,140
Unfortunately, there's really
nothing I can do about it.

305
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:10,010
He'll have some difficulty
using his right arm,

306
00:17:10,010 --> 00:17:11,290
and I'm afraid that, well,

307
00:17:11,290 --> 00:17:15,150
he'll never be able to hold
a sword in his hand again.

308
00:17:15,150 --> 00:17:17,010
Oh no.

309
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:19,130
This is so unfair, the one
thing he loved in this world

310
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:21,260
was Kendo and now he can't
even practice it anymore.

311
00:17:21,260 --> 00:17:25,000
Ugh, this really stinks!

312
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,030
Raijuta!

313
00:17:27,030 --> 00:17:30,000
I hope you rot in hell!

314
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:35,200
(birds chirping)

315
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:40,020
Hey, Kori, is there
any news about Yutaro?

316
00:17:40,020 --> 00:17:41,120
I heard he didn't
go out of his room

317
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:43,280
for a month after the incident.

318
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:45,030
Well, who can blame him?

319
00:17:45,030 --> 00:17:46,180
He can't practice
a sword anymore,

320
00:17:46,180 --> 00:17:49,130
and he treated Raijuta
like a father.

321
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:51,150
What a horrible thing to happen.

322
00:17:51,150 --> 00:17:53,010
He can't trust anyone anymore,

323
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:55,040
it must seem like his
whole life is ruined.

324
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:57,030
Kori, I feel so helpless!

325
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:59,200
Isn't there anything
we can do to help him?

326
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:02,130
Isn't there anything
in our training?

327
00:18:02,130 --> 00:18:04,060
I'm afraid there isn't.

328
00:18:04,060 --> 00:18:07,230
I really wish there was
something we could do for him.

329
00:18:07,230 --> 00:18:08,230
Megumi.

330
00:18:08,230 --> 00:18:11,190
Everyone's so sad, it
feels like a funeral.

331
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:15,030
We're sad Megumi because we
were talking about Yutaro.

332
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:16,080
Then this should cheer you up,

333
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:18,040
we just got a
letter from Yutaro.

334
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,080
Huh?

335
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:22,050
What?

336
00:18:22,050 --> 00:18:24,080
"Dear friends at
the Kamiya Dojo,

337
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,250
how is everyone?

338
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:27,280
I'm writing to thank
you for all you've done,

339
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,190
and let you know
that I'm moving."

340
00:18:29,190 --> 00:18:31,050
-Huh?
-What's that?

341
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:33,100
"I'm moving to Germany
where my uncle lives."

342
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:35,060
Huh, he's moving where?

343
00:18:35,060 --> 00:18:37,200
"I think it should be
more peaceful there.

344
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:39,060
I wanna forget
all the bad things

345
00:18:39,060 --> 00:18:41,130
that have happened
to me in Japan.

346
00:18:41,130 --> 00:18:44,140
I don't think that
I will ever return."

347
00:18:44,140 --> 00:18:45,240
Yutaro.

348
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:52,230
♪

349
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:56,210
The young master's uncle knows
a very good doctor in Germany.

350
00:18:56,210 --> 00:18:59,020
He believes that this
doctor could be a big help

351
00:18:59,020 --> 00:19:01,120
and heal Yutaro's arm.

352
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:05,070
I certainly hope so.

353
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:06,250
That's great.

354
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:10,170
Yutaro, just as soon as that
doctor fixes your arm up,

355
00:19:10,170 --> 00:19:12,250
you'll have to come
back here and visit us.

356
00:19:12,250 --> 00:19:16,030
We at the Kamiya Dojo will
always welcome you, okay?

357
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:21,000
♪

358
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,040
Yutaro?

359
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,230
I suppose we should
be getting along,

360
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:25,160
the ship will be leaving soon.

361
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:27,030
Thank you very much
for seeing us off.

362
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:28,250
It means a lot to
the young master,

363
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:31,030
and thank you all for
everything you've done.

364
00:19:31,030 --> 00:19:32,160
Please take care.

365
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:35,110
We must be going.

366
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:37,000
So long, Yutaro!

367
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,130
Please write us, and let
us know how you're doing.

368
00:19:39,130 --> 00:19:43,190
♪

369
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:45,290
Hey, Yutaro!

370
00:19:45,290 --> 00:19:47,200
Hey, think fast!

371
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,260
(grunting)

372
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:51,120
Yoshi!

373
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,140
Loser!

374
00:19:52,140 --> 00:19:54,030
You think you could
sneak out of the country,

375
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:55,130
and forget our fight?

376
00:19:55,130 --> 00:19:57,090
What--why you!

377
00:19:57,090 --> 00:20:00,120
We had a deal, and I expect you
to keep your end of the bargain!

378
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:04,260
Unless of course if you're
afraid to fight me, is that it?

379
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:07,190
Do you think that just
because you got your arm hurt

380
00:20:07,190 --> 00:20:10,140
that you don't have to
keep your word any longer?

381
00:20:10,140 --> 00:20:12,110
Well, that's not the
way it works here!

382
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,250
Oh?

383
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:16,200
Now, either you get well,
and come back here and fight,

384
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,160
or you're a loser.

385
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,090
(grunting)

386
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:21,270
Oh, yeah?

387
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:24,290
I will get well, and
come back and fight you!

388
00:20:24,290 --> 00:20:27,160
If I have to I'll fight
you with my left arm.

389
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:28,240
And you know something?

390
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:31,040
With my left arm
I could take you.

391
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:33,200
I'm not afraid of
you or anything else!

392
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:36,000
-Then prove it!
-I will!

393
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,260
I'll be back here
to trounce you good!

394
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:39,010
That I'd like to see!

395
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:40,190
Come back here if
you're not too chicken!

396
00:20:40,190 --> 00:20:43,250
♪

397
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,230
Oh, well.

398
00:20:44,230 --> 00:20:46,270
Looks like everything's
back to normal.

399
00:20:46,270 --> 00:20:49,150
♪

400
00:20:49,150 --> 00:20:51,200
So, Yutaro sailed
halfway around the world

401
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:55,220
to Germany to live
with his uncle.

402
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:57,140
Hey!

403
00:20:57,140 --> 00:20:59,070
Don't you forget!

404
00:20:59,070 --> 00:21:01,100
You and I have to
settle the score!

405
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:03,290
Didn't think I'd let you
off that easy, did ya?

406
00:21:03,290 --> 00:21:06,210
(boat engine whirring)

407
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:09,070
(birds chirping)

408
00:21:09,070 --> 00:21:11,150
So long, Yoshi!

409
00:21:11,150 --> 00:21:14,170
I will beat you, my friend,
when I come back here.

410
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:17,020
♪

411
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:19,150
That day, another name was
added to the list of names

412
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:21,090
at our Kamiya Dojo.

413
00:21:21,090 --> 00:21:24,010
♪

414
00:21:24,010 --> 00:21:26,130
He was one student
I'll never forget.

415
00:21:26,130 --> 00:21:28,070
♪

416
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:30,220
Yutaro Tsukayama.

417
00:21:30,220 --> 00:21:34,290
♪

418
00:21:36,010 --> 00:23:11,010
♪

